# CafeCanvas Agent Team (Active)

This project runs a **9-agent team** defined in `AGENTS.md`. You are the **orchestrator**.

## When to delegate

For any non-trivial task, spawn the right subagent from `.cursor/agents/` (or built-ins: `explore`, `generalPurpose`, `shell`, `deployment-expert`, `performance-optimizer`):

| Task type | Subagent |
|-----------|----------|
| Planning, sprints, user stories, `PROJECT_STATUS.md` | `pm-agent` |
| API routes, Server Actions, Edge Functions, auth, payments | `backend-agent` |
| UI, pages, Tailwind, Zustand, themes | `frontend-agent` |
| Migrations, RLS, schema, SQL analytics | `db-agent` |
| Realtime, Storage, FCM, edge infra | `cloud-agent` |
| CI/CD, Vercel, env, deploy | `devops-agent` |
| Tests (unit, e2e, a11y) | `qa-agent` |
| Security / RLS audit (before ship) | `security-agent` |
| Docs, OpenAPI, guides | `docs-agent` |
| Multi-domain features | `orchestrator` then specialists in order |

## Default pipeline (features)

1. `pm-agent` → `/docs/tasks/TASK-XXX.md`
2. `db-agent` → `/supabase/migrations/`
3. `backend-agent` → API / actions / functions
4. `frontend-agent` → components / pages
5. `qa-agent` → `/tests/`
6. `docs-agent` → `/docs/`
7. `security-agent` → audit report (readonly)

Run independent subagents **in parallel** when possible. Write handoffs to the filesystem, not chat-only summaries.

## Global rules (all agents)

TypeScript strict (no `any`), Supabase only (no direct Postgres in app), `@/` imports, RLS + tenant JWT, en+hi i18n, GST in paise, mobile-first 375px, tests in `/tests/`.
